   "source": [
    "Given that data is higly correalted and distributions are overlapping, I will be using PCA to extract the features that are responsible for most variance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Seperating Response variable from dataframe"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_type = df.type\n",
    "df.drop('type',axis=1,inplace=True)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Splitting data to train test in the ratio of 80:20"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 23,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(df, np.ravel(df_type), test_size=0.20, random_state=101,stratify=df_type)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Data is split in 80:20, to give the maximum chance of generalization and fitting while mainting integrity of validation\n",
    "Random state is used to be able to repeat the same result when applied again.\n",
    "Stratify is to distribute classes equally among test and training data as classes are imbalanced."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Standardizing data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 24,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "sc = StandardScaler()\n",
    "X_train = sc.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test = sc.transform(X_test)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "#### Applying PCA"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 25,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([[ 2.14553244, -0.07203287, -0.07048006, ...,  0.91414999,\n",

   "cell_type": "code",

   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [

      "0.9605541969176709\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "explained_variance = pca.explained_variance_ratio_\n",
    "print(explained_variance)\n",
    "print(explained_variance[0:3].sum())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The first 3 principle components are able to explain 96% variance in the data. So I am considering the first components as features."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 27,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "\n",
    "pca = PCA(n_components=3)\n",
    "X_train = pca.fit_transform(X_train)\n",
    "X_test = pca.transform(X_test)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now that X_train and X_test are prepared, fitting SVM, Random Forrest and XGBoost Classifiers on the data and compare results. These classifiers are selected because they work with imbalanced and non-linear data."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [

    "#XGBoost\n",
    "from xgboost import XGBClassifier\n",
    "\n",
    "#GridSearchCV\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import RandomizedSearchCV\n",
    "\n",
    "#metrics\n",

    "from sklearn.metrics import plot_confusion_matrix\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import RocCurveDisplay\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import auc"
   ]

    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Function to get Sensitivity, specificity and precision"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 40,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_metrics(cnf_matrix,columns= ['Metric','P','R','SO','SW','T','W']):\n",
    "    FP = cnf_matrix.sum(axis=0) - np.diag(cnf_matrix) \n",
    "    FN = cnf_matrix.sum(axis=1) - np.diag(cnf_matrix)\n",
    "    TP = np.diag(cnf_matrix)\n",
    "    TN = cnf_matrix.sum() - (FP + FN + TP)\n",
    "    FP = FP.astype(float)\n",
    "    FN = FN.astype(float)\n",
    "    TP = TP.astype(float)\n",
    "    TN = TN.astype(float)\n",
    "    \n",
    "    df = pd.DataFrame(columns=columns)\n",
    "    row_list = []\n",
    "    # Sensitivity, hit rate, recall, or true positive rate\n",
    "    TPR = TP/(TP+FN)\n",
    "    row_list.append(np.append('Sensitivity',np.round(TPR,2)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Specificity or true negative rate\n",
    "    TNR = TN/(TN+FP)\n",
    "    row_list.append(np.append('Specificity',np.round(TNR,2)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Precision or positive predictive value\n",
    "    PPV = TP/(TP+FP)\n",
    "    row_list.append(np.append('Precision',np.round(PPV,2)))\n",
    "    \n",
    "    return pd.DataFrame(row_list, columns=columns)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 41,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/html": [
       "<div>\n",
       "<style scoped>\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th:only-of-type {\n",
       "        vertical-align: middle;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe tbody tr th {\n",
       "        vertical-align: top;\n",
       "    }\n",
       "\n",
       "    .dataframe thead th {\n",
       "        text-align: right;\n",

       "</style>\n",

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### ROC curve"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 109,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def plot_multiclass_roc(clf, X_test, y_test, n_classes, figsize=(17, 6), name=\"Model\"):\n",
    "    if name=='SVM':\n",
    "        y_score = clf.decision_function(X_test)\n",
    "    else:\n",
    "        y_score = clf.predict_proba(X_test)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # structures\n",
    "    fpr = dict()\n",
    "    tpr = dict()\n",
    "    roc_auc = dict()\n",
    "\n",
    "    # calculate dummies once\n",
    "    encoder = pd.get_dummies(y_test, drop_first=False)\n",
    "    y_test_dummies = encoder.values\n",
    "    for i in range(n_classes):\n",
    "        fpr[i], tpr[i], _ = roc_curve(y_test_dummies[:, i], y_score[:, i])\n",
    "        roc_auc[i] = auc(fpr[i], tpr[i])\n",
    "\n",
    "    # roc for each class\n",
    "    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=figsize)\n",
    "    ax.plot([0, 1], [0, 1], 'k--')\n",
    "    ax.set_xlim([0.0, 1.0])\n",
    "    ax.set_ylim([0.0, 1.05])\n",
    "    ax.set_xlabel('False Positive Rate')\n",
    "    ax.set_ylabel('True Positive Rate')\n",
    "    ax.set_title('Receiver operating characteristic curve for {}'.format(name))\n",
    "    for i in range(n_classes):\n",
    "        ax.plot(fpr[i], tpr[i], label='ROC curve (area = %0.2f) for type %s' % (roc_auc[i], encoder.columns.tolist()[i]))\n",
    "    ax.legend(loc=\"best\")\n",
    "    ax.grid(alpha=.4)\n",
    "    sns.despine()\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 110,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1152x720 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plot_multiclass_roc(svm_grid, X_test, y_test, n_classes=6, figsize=(16, 10),name = \"SVM\")"
   ]
